President Trump addressed the military personnel at Osan Air Base in Pyeongtaek, Republic of Korea. He thanked them for their service and highlighted the importance of their role in national security. Trump mentioned his recent meeting with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un and the progress being made towards resolving the issues between the two countries. He also expressed his pride in the strength and capabilities of the US military and emphasized his commitment to providing them with the best equipment and resources. Trump concluded by thanking the military for their dedication and sacrifice, and wished them a happy Independence Day.